This paper deals with the logical reconstruction of SPKI/SDSI, which is a proposed public key infrastructure standard. The paper discusses the use of local names, revocation, expiry dates, and tuple reduction in SPKI. These topics are closely related to computer security (cs.CR), logic (cs.LO), software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), and data structures (cs.DS). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
